Start
/ Compile one step. Planner gave us the set of actions involved via planStep.actions;
/ the compiler decides chain order, fills parameters, and emits the .pr actions array.
/ Retry semantics are delegated to error.handle (built-in RetryCount, GoalFirst order).

- set %step% = %goal.Steps[planStep.index]%
- call Compile


Compile
/ Validate planner's action set against runtime catalog + augment with explicit
/ module.action tokens from step text. Drops hallucinated entries; appends any
/ literal `module.action` mention the planner missed. See building-the-builder.md
/ "preventing self-rebuild corruption" for the rationale.
- builder.validateStepActions step=%step%, actions=%planStep.actions%, write to %planStep.actions%
- builder.actions actions=%planStep.actions%, write to %actions%
- builder.types actions=%planStep.actions%, write to %typeInfo%
/ Per-step so the snapshot reflects the Actions just written by prior BuildSteps.
- goal.getTypes Goal=%goal%, write to %varTypes%
- set %stepVarTypes% = %varTypes[step.Index]%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/templates/stepForLlm.template", write to %stepForLlm%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/templates/stepActionDetails.template", write to %actionDetails%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/Compile.llm", write to %buildStepPrompt%
- render template "/system/builder/llm/CompileUser.llm", write to %buildStepUserMsg%
- set %messages% = [{"Role":"system", "Content":"%buildStepPrompt%"}, {"Role":"user", "Content":"%buildStepUserMsg%"}], type=json

/ QueryAndVerify wraps llm.query + a missing-actions check (throws on missing-actions).
/ on error key="missing-actions": run RefineActions first (expands %planStep.actions%),
/ then retry the whole QueryAndVerify. RetryCount is the runtime's job, no counter.
- call QueryAndVerify, on error key "missing-actions" call RefineActions, then retry 2 times

/ system prompt is stashed once at goal level (%trace.compileSystem%) — do not duplicate it here.
- add {goal: %goal.Name%, index: %step.Index%, stepText: %step.Text%, actions: %planStep.actions%, user: %buildStepUserMsg%, response: %compileResult%, usage: {model: %compileResult.Model%, promptTokens: %compileResult.PromptTokens%, cachedTokens: %compileResult.CachedTokens%, completionTokens: %compileResult.CompletionTokens%, totalTokens: %compileResult.TotalTokens%, cost: %compileResult.Cost%, cached: %compileResult.Cached%}} to %trace.stepPasses%

- set %goal.Steps[step.Index].Actions% = %compileResult.actions%
- set %goal.Steps[step.Index].Formal% = %compileResult.formal%

/ Validation retry: FixValidation re-queries the LLM with the validator's complaint as
/ previousConversation context, writes the corrected compileResult, updates goal.Steps.
/ Then retry builder.validate against the corrected actions.
- builder.validate actions=%goal.Steps[step.Index].Actions%, on error call FixValidation, then retry 2 times

- if %!build.summary% is true, call EmitSummary


QueryAndVerify
- llm.query Messages=%messages%, Schema={formal: string, actions: [{module: string, action: string, parameters?: [{name: string, value?: object, type?: string}], errors?: [{key: string, message: string}]}], errors?: [{key: string, message: string}]}, cache=%!build.cache%, on error call HandleStepFailure, write to %compileResult%
- if %compileResult.errors[0].key% is "missing-actions", throw error "missing-actions: %compileResult.errors[0].message%" key="missing-actions"


RefineActions
/ Planner continuation: hand the LLM the compiler's complaint, get an expanded action set.
- set %complaint% = "Compiler returned missing-actions for step %step.Index% (text: '%step.Text%'). Current action set is insufficient: %planStep.actions%. Reason: %!error.Message%. Return a corrected action set for step %step.Index% only.", type=string
- set %refineMessages% = [{"Role":"user", "Content":"%complaint%"}], type=json
- llm.query Messages=%refineMessages%, Schema={index: int, actions: [string]}, cache=%!build.cache%, previousConversation=%plan%, write to %correction%
- set %planStep.actions% = %correction.actions%
- set %trace.plan.steps[step.Index].actions% = %correction.actions%
- write out "  Step %step.Index% missing-actions — expanding set"


FixValidation
/ Validator rejected the compiled actions. Re-prompt the LLM with the validator's
/ complaint, write corrected compileResult, update goal.Steps so the subsequent retry
/ of builder.validate sees the corrected actions.
- set %fixMessages% = [{"Role":"user", "Content":"Your previous response was rejected by the validator: %!error.Message%\n\nReturn the corrected response in the same Output Shape (formal, actions, errors, warnings) for this step only."}], type=json
- llm.query Messages=%fixMessages%, Schema={formal: string, actions: [{module: string, action: string, parameters?: [{name: string, value?: object, type?: string}], modifiers?: [{module: string, action: string, parameters?: [{name: string, value?: object, type?: string}]}], errors?: [{key: string, message: string}]}], errors?: [{key: string, message: string}]}, cache=%!build.cache%, previousConversation=%compileResult%, write to %compileResult%
- set %goal.Steps[step.Index].Actions% = %compileResult.actions%
- set %goal.Steps[step.Index].Formal% = %compileResult.formal%
- write out "  Step %step.Index% validation error — retrying: %!error.Message%"


HandleStepFailure
- write out "  Step %step.Index% build error: %!error.Message%"
- throw %!error%


EmitSummary
/ One line per step. [≡] for cache hits, [✓] for fresh.
- if %compileResult.Cached% is true, output.write Data="  [≡] %step.Text%",
- if %compileResult.Cached% is not true, output.write Data="  [✓] %step.Text%",
